\begin_layout Standard
The data in all modern output files are referenced to Coordinated Universal
 Time (UTC), although there are some exceptions in old archived data files.
 The system time and date are synchronized to the Global Positioning System
 (GPS) at the beginning of each flight, and for data acquired by the present
 ADS-3 (NIDAS) data acquisition system time is synchronized continuously
 with the GPS time.
 Time variables are often different for older archived data files; some
 of the following are obsolete, but are included here for reference because
 they are important to those wanting to use those archives.
