This is the reference time for the NETCDF output data files (data system
 versions before ADS-3).
 It represents the time of the first data record.
 Its format is Unix time (elapsed seconds after midnight 1 January 1970).
 Use this measurement and add time_offset to obtain the time for each data
 record.
 (Note: base_time is a single scalar, not a 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

record
\begin_inset Quotes erd
